original_result.user_prompt: What's VT100 code to render green terminal text?
original_result.completion_text:
The VT100 code to render green terminal text uses the ANSI escape sequence for setting the foreground color to green. In this case, the code is "\033[32m", where "\033" represents the escape character, "[", followed by "32", which specifies the color green, and finally "m" marks the end of the escape sequence.

Here's an example demonstrating its usage in Python:

```python
print("\033[32mThis text will be displayed in green.\033[0m")
```

When executed, the output will display the message "This text will be displayed in green." in green color within the terminal. Note that the "\033[0m" resets the formatting back to default after displaying the colored text.
